10. Database Replication Models

A. Master-Slave (Primary-Secondary)

* Primary handles writes.
* Replicas handle reads.

Asynchronous

* Low write latency.
* Eventual Consistency.
* Possible replication lag.

Synchronous

* Strong consistency.
* Higher write latency.

Advantages:

* High Read Scalability
* High Availability
* No Write Conflicts

B. Master-Master

* Multiple nodes can read and write.
* Bi-directional replication.

Advantages:

* High Availability
* Read + Write Scalability

Disadvantages:

* Write Conflicts
* Transaction Ordering Issues

--------------------------------------------------------------

