13. Asynchronous Processing

* Tasks processed later through queues.
* Reduces write load on database.
* Smooths traffic spikes.

Example:
Order Request
↓
Message Queue
↓
Order Processing Service

Benefits:

* Better scalability
* Better resource utilization

-----------------------------------------------------------

14. Caching

* Stores frequently accessed data.
* Reduces latency.
* Reduces database load.

Types:

* Browser Cache
* HTTP Cache
* Session Cache
* Object Cache
* Redis Cache
* Memcached

--------------------------------------------------------------

15. Partitioning

A. Vertical Partitioning

* Split system by functionality.
* Common in Microservices.

Example:
User Service → User DB
Order Service → Order DB
Catalog Service → Catalog DB

Benefits:

* Independent scaling
* Better modularity

Challenge:

* No ACID transactions across services.
* Eventual consistency required.

--------------------------------------------------------------

B. Horizontal Partitioning (Sharding)

* Split data across multiple databases.

Example:

Node 1 → IDs 1-100
Node 2 → IDs 101-200
Node 3 → IDs 201-300

Benefits:

* Higher scalability
* Better storage distribution

--------------------------------------------------------------

16. Sharding Techniques

A. Range Partitioning

Node 1 → 1-100
Node 2 → 101-200
Node 3 → 201-300

Good for:

* Range queries

B. Hash Partitioning

Hash(ID) % N

Good for:

* Even distribution of data

--------------------------------------------------------------

17. Routing in Sharding

Methods:

A. Client Library Routing

* Client knows shard location.

B. Router/Proxy Routing

* Request goes to router.
* Router forwards to correct shard.

